Unfortunately, this Udemy course falls short of expectations. The didactic approach is inadequate, focusing almost entirely on a rapid, superficial walkthrough of pre-written code. Instead of a structured presentation that explains fundamental concepts, the course lacks visual aids such as slides or whiteboard explanations. The instructor navigates through the code far too quickly, making it nearly impossible to grasp the context. There's no explanation of what the Python code does in the background or the logical reasoning behind the chosen syntax. This makes the learning process purely mechanical and prevents the development of a deeper understanding. Even with prior knowledge from another Python course, many things remained unclear. The entire course feels confusing and poorly structured. It seems the primary goal is not to teach but to promote the instructor's LinkedIn profile. This approach undermines the course's credibility and makes it unsuitable for serious learners who want to build a solid foundation of knowledge.

Over roughly six weeks you don’t just watch lectures—you actually create eight different projects, from digital twins to multi-agent trading systems, using modern frameworks like LangGraph, CrewAI, and the new MCP protocol.

Instructor was very knowledgeable and excited about the topic. His enthusiasm was contagious. I felt that the subject matter was interesting but some of the examples were a little less real-life, e.g. the stock trading app. What could have been done better is understanding the pre-requisites for computer setup, especially for Windows users. It seemed like we were installing a couple hundred megabytes of software every few days. Having to install WSL was a major hassle and even then the code had to be tweaked several times (thank you ChatGPT) to make it work. Also, having to sign up for so many third-party tools was time consuming. Finally, the course says "Master AI Agents in 30 days" - that's 30 course days, not the same as 1 month. Why this matters: the Pushover free account that is used very early in the course is only free for 1 month. This course takes at least 6 weeks to complete, unless you plan on working on it Saturday and Sunday. Overall, the course was well worth my time though.
